            <!-- TEMPLATE ZONE: EXAMPLE "REPLICABLE BLOCKS" INSTRUCTIONS      -->
            <!-- ============================================================= -->
            <div class="instruction-panel">
                <h3>📋 how to replicate & contribute (team workflow)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>➕ Add a pet for a friend:</strong> copy a
                        <code>&lt;div class="pet-card"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</code> block, paste inside the
                        <code>.pets-collection</code> of your teammate's section, then change name, type, color and
                        emoji/image.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>➕ Add a new interest:</strong> copy <code>&lt;li&gt;...&lt;/li&gt;</code> inside the
                        <code>.interests-list</code> of any person.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>➕ Create an entirely new section:</strong> copy a whole
                        <code>&lt;div class="extra-creative"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</code> and paste it before the closing
                        <code>&lt;/section&gt;</code> of a person card. Customize the heading and text to reflect a new
                        fact (e.g., "favorite games", "dream travel").
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>➕ Add a new person (new group member):</strong> copy the whole
                        <code>&lt;section class="person-card"&gt;...&lt;/section&gt;</code> from any existing member and
                        paste before <code>&lt;/main&gt;</code>. Fill in all sub-blocks (avatar, usernames, aspirations,
                        interests, pets).
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="tiny-note">⭐ Pro tip: For a self-portrait image instead of animated emoji, replace the
                    <code>.avatar-icon</code> div with
                    <code>&lt;img class="avatar-img" src="your-image-url.jpg" alt="portrait"&gt;</code>. Use any icon
                    library or GIF for animated characters!
                </p>
            </div>

